# .gitignore — Data Fortress
# ---------------------------
# Tells Git which files and directories to never track.
# Organised by tool/language for easy scanning.

# ── Rust / Cargo ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# The target/ directory holds ALL compiled output — debug objects, release
# binaries, incremental build caches, doc output, test binaries. It can be
# several GB and is fully reproducible from source, so we never commit it.
/target/

# Cargo.lock is committed for binary projects (it pins exact dependency versions,
# which makes builds reproducible on other machines). For library crates it's
# usually omitted. Data Fortress is a binary, so Cargo.lock IS tracked.
# (No rule here — absence of a rule means "track it".)

# ── Python / Streamlit ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Python bytecode caches — generated automatically, not portable between machines.
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class

# Virtual environments — each developer creates their own.
.venv/
venv/
env/

# Pytest / coverage artefacts.
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/

# mypy type-check cache.
.mypy_cache/

# Streamlit's own cache directory (stores cached function results on disk).
.streamlit/

# ── Database and user data ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# SQLite database files — created at runtime by `data-fortress scan`.
# Never commit a user's actual database; it contains personal file metadata.
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3

# Backup archives produced by `data-fortress backup create`.
*.tar.zst
*.zst

# Undo logs written by `data-fortress organize`.
.fortress_undo.json

# ── Editor / IDE ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# VS Code workspace settings (project-local overrides are personal preference).
.vscode/

# JetBrains IDEs (CLion, PyCharm, IntelliJ).
.idea/

# Vim swap files.
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# macOS metadata files (if anyone ever touches this on a Mac).
.DS_Store

# ── Secrets and local config ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Environment variable files — often contain API keys or local paths.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Local config overrides (non-XDG paths, development test paths).
config.local.json

# ── Test artefacts ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Temporary directories created by integration tests using the `tempfile` crate.
/tmp/fortress-test-*/

# ── Documentation build output ────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Rust docs built by `cargo doc` or `make doc`.
/doc/
